    • Method Detail

      • unbounded

        public static <T> AsyncQueue<T> unbounded​()
        Creates an unbounded AsyncQueue.

        Sends on an unbounded queue always complete synchronously, and throttling must be managed by the senders to ensure senders don't get too far ahead of the consumer. See AsyncQueue for details.

        Returns:
        an AsyncQueue
        See Also:
        AsyncQueue

      • bounded

        public static <T> BoundedAsyncQueue<T> bounded​()
        Creates a bounded AsyncQueue.

        This queue can only accept one value at a time until it is consumed. This may be useful when you want to produce work potentially in parallel, but want to be throttled at the rate at which you can consume this work. See BoundedAsyncQueue for details.

        Returns:
        a BoundedAsyncQueue

      • buffered

        public static <T> BoundedAsyncQueue<T> buffered​(int maxBuffer)
        Creates a buffered AsyncQueue.

        This queue can accept up to maxBuffer values before the futures returned by send become delayed. See BoundedAsyncQueue for details

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of elements in the returned queue
        Parameters:
        maxBuffer - the maximum number of values that the queue will accept before applying backpressure to senders
        Returns:
        a BoundedAsyncQueue with a buffer size of maxBuffer elements
